<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><h1>Follow the games here: <a href="https://www.chess.com/events/2023-sharjah-chess-masters">Chess.com</a> | <a href="https://chess24.com/en/watch/live-tournaments/sharjah-masters-2023">Chess24</a></h1> <p><strong>SHARJAH</strong> - The 6th Sharjah Masters International Chess Championship will kick off at Sharjah Cultural &amp; Chess Club, with the participation of 80 players. The championship will be held under the patronage of His Highness Dr Sheikh Sultan Bin Mohammed Al Qasimi, Supreme Council Member and Ruler of Sharjah, and organized by the Sharjah Cultural &amp; Chess Club.</p> <p>The extremely diverse field has both talented youngsters like Hans Niemann, Gukesh D, Arjun Erigiasi, R Praggnanandhaa, Sameul Sevian, Andrey Esipenko, Nihal Sarin, all eager for glory as well as experienced veterans such as Yu Yangyi, Vidit Gujrathi, Ray Robson, Women&#39;s World Champion Ju Wenjun and the UAE&#39;s own Salem Saleh.</p> <p>Boasting 8 players over 2700+ and several more potentially under-rated prodigies, the all Grandmaster field of 78 players is quite possibly the strongest invitational open tournament in chess history.</p> <h2>Top Participants</h2> <table><thead> <tr> <th align="left"><strong>#</strong></th> <th align="left"><strong>Title</strong></th> <th align="left"><strong>Name</strong></th> <th align="left"><strong>FED</strong></th> <th align="left"><strong>Elo</strong></th> <th align="left">Score</th> </tr> </thead><tbody> <tr> <td align="left">1</td> <td align="left">GM</td> <td align="left">Parham Maghsoodloo</td> <td align="left">ðŸ‡®ðŸ‡· IRN</td> <td align="left">2734</td> <td align="left">0</td> </tr> <tr> <td align="left">2</td> <td align="left">GM</td> <td align="left">Gukesh D</td> <td align="left">ðŸ‡®ðŸ‡³ IND</td> <td align="left">2732</td> <td align="left">0</td> </tr> <tr> <td align="left">3</td> <td align="left">GM</td> <td align="left">Vidit Gujrathi</td> <td align="left">ðŸ‡®ðŸ‡³ IND</td> <td align="left">2731</t